Treat `opts` as overrides when it is a *proper keyword list* — that is, when every
element is a two-element tuple `{key, value}` whose `key` is an atom. In that case
return `{[], opts}` (no traits, all overrides). Otherwise (e.g. a list of bare
atoms like `[:admin]`) treat the whole list as traits and return `{opts, []}` (no
overrides). Note that an empty list qualifies as a proper keyword list, so it
yields `{[], []}`.

